# Parallel subagents when possible

When planning work, **default to parallelism** for independent slices: run **multiple subagents in the same turn** (each with its own bounded task and prompt) instead of doing the same exploration sequentially.

## Do parallelize

- Broad codebase discovery across **different** areas (e.g. API vs web vs schema).
- Several **read-only** investigations (search, map files, answer “where does X live?”).
- Isolated tasks with **no shared mutable files** in the same step (e.g. one agent per package or domain).

Each parallel subagent must get a **self-contained prompt** (they do not see the parent chat). Include paths, goals, and what to return.

## Do not parallelize

- Step B **depends on** step A’s result (order matters).
- Multiple agents would **edit the same files** or race the same resource in one pass.
- A **single small** change where spawning agents adds overhead without benefit.

## Practical default

If you would otherwise run **two or more independent searches or explorations** one after another, **batch them as parallel subagents** instead.
